The paper deals with independence of infinite words based on finite-state automata, which falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The concept of compression and transducers with auxiliary input suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the study of normal words, which is related to combinatorics on words (cs.DS). The proof techniques used in the paper involve measure theory, which is a topic in mathematical logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper deals with the construction of a specific type of word, which could be seen as a problem in computational complexity (cs.CC).
